---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 220
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Death=The Destruction of I-Consciousness
  - 143
By: Bâyazid al Bistâmi
---
I went to pray with the devotees, and did not feel in my place. I went
among those who mortify themselves, ... among those who fast, and
still I did not feel in my place. I said, ‘O my God! what then is the
way to thee?’ And the answer given me was, ‘Abandon thyself and come.’
